flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Start of recall campaign or periodic inventory review.]
  A --> N1[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Forecast recall parts demand using historical data and campaign timelines.]
  N1 --> N2[PB: Remote Functions - Generate purchase orders to suppliers based on forecasted demand.]
  N2 --> N3[Stream: STREAMS - Monitor inventory levels across locations to ensure adequate stock.]
  N3 --> N4[PB: Process Builder - Coordinate logistics to distribute recall parts to dealerships.]
  N4 --> N5[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Capture defective part returns for engineering analysis.]
  N5 --> N6{PB: CWB Lifecycle - Decide disposition paths for obsolete/surplus parts.}
  N6 -->|Primary| P1[Action: Generate purchase orders, maintain inventory levels, coordinate logistics, capture returns, and decide disposition paths.]
  P1 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced working capital, minimized stockouts, improved OTIF, lower COGS, and optimized EBITDA.]
  N6 -->|Inventory levels fall below threshold.| B1[Trigger emergency order from suppliers.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Prevent stockouts and ensure timely delivery.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N6 -->|Logistics costs exceed budget.| B2[Re-optimize distribution routes and methods.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Minimize logistics expenses while maintaining OTIF.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N6 -->|High volume of defective part returns.| B3[Initiate engineering analysis and expedite remediation.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Address quality issues promptly and reduce future defects.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]